---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
const kind = Astro.url.pathname.includes('battery') ? 'battery' : Astro.url.pathname.includes('accessory') ? 'budget' : 'storage';
const title = kind === 'battery' ? 'Steam Deck and handheld battery life estimator' : kind === 'budget' ? 'Handheld gaming accessory budget calculator' : 'Steam Deck storage calculator and game library planner';
const description = kind === 'battery' ? 'Estimate Steam Deck, ROG Ally, Legion Go, and handheld gaming battery life from watt-hours, system draw, and a safety buffer.' : kind === 'budget' ? 'Plan a Steam Deck, ROG Ally, or Legion Go accessory budget for storage, docks, chargers, cases, controllers, and travel gear.' : 'Estimate how many games fit on Steam Deck and handheld PC storage after reserving space for updates, shader caches, saves, and overhead.';
const path = kind === 'battery' ? 'battery-estimator' : kind === 'budget' ? 'accessory-budget' : 'storage-planner';
const faq = kind === 'battery' ? [
  ['How do I estimate handheld battery life?','Divide usable battery watt-hours by estimated total system draw. The result is a planning estimate; display brightness, wireless use, battery health, and game load change runtime.'],
  ['What wattage should I enter?','Use measured total system draw when available. A device TDP value alone does not include the display, memory, storage, cooling, and conversion losses.'],
  ['How can I extend Steam Deck or ROG Ally battery life?','Use a stable frame cap, lower brightness, reduce the power target gradually, and lower expensive graphics effects.']
] : kind === 'budget' ? [
  ['What accessories should I buy first?','Start with storage and a reliable charger, then add protection, a dock, controller, or travel gear only when it solves a real problem.'],
  ['Should I budget for a dock immediately?','Not necessarily. Buy a dock when you know you will use a TV, monitor, Ethernet, keyboard, mouse, or external storage.'],
  ['Are the gear links affiliate links?','Amazon links are marked sponsored. If our tracking ID is active, we may earn from qualifying purchases at no extra cost to you.']
] : [
  ['How many games fit on a 512GB Steam Deck?','It depends on average game size and reserved free space. Enter your own library average rather than relying on a single generic count.'],
  ['Why reserve free storage?','Updates, shader caches, saves, screenshots, temporary patch files, launchers, and operating-system overhead all use space beyond the headline install size.'],
  ['Should I buy a microSD card or SSD?','A microSD card is the simplest expansion. An internal SSD can be faster or larger, but requires device-specific fit checks, backup planning, and opening the handheld.']
];
const jsonLd = [
  {'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'SoftwareApplication',name:title,applicationCategory:'UtilitiesApplication',operatingSystem:'Web',url:`https://handheldsettings.com/calculators/${path}/`,offers:{'@type':'Offer',price:'0',priceCurrency:'USD'},description},
  {'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'FAQPage',mainEntity:faq.map(([q,a])=>({'@type':'Question',name:q,acceptedAnswer:{'@type':'Answer',text:a}}))}
];
---
<Base title={`${title} — Handheld Settings Lab`} description={description} jsonLd={jsonLd}>
<section class="section"><div class="wrap article"><span class="eyebrow">Free handheld gaming calculator</span><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede muted">{description} Numbers are planning estimates, not manufacturer claims or guaranteed results.</p><div class="card calc">
{kind === 'storage' && <><label for="a">Total storage GB</label><input id="a" type="number" value="512" min="1"/><label for="b">Average game size GB</label><input id="b" type="number" value="35" min="1"/><label for="c">Reserve space GB</label><input id="c" type="number" value="60" min="0"/></>}
{kind === 'battery' && <><label for="a">Battery watt-hours</label><input id="a" type="number" value="50" min="1"/><label for="b">Estimated total system draw watts</label><input id="b" type="number" value="15" min="1"/><label for="c">Safety buffer %</label><input id="c" type="number" value="10" min="0" max="90"/></>}
{kind === 'budget' && <><label for="a">microSD / SSD budget</label><input id="a" type="number" value="80" min="0"/><label for="b">Dock / charger budget</label><input id="b" type="number" value="70" min="0"/><label for="c">Case / controller budget</label><input id="c" type="number" value="90" min="0"/></>}
<div class="result" aria-live="polite"><strong id="out">Calculating…</strong><p class="muted" id="hint"></p></div></div>
<h2>How to use this estimate</h2>{kind === 'storage' && <><p>Use the capacity available to games—not only the marketed drive size. Set average game size from the games you actually play. A cozy or indie library may average under 10GB, while a modern AAA library can average 70–120GB or more.</p><p>Reserve enough space for game updates, shader caches, save data, screenshots, temporary patch files, and launcher overhead. Keeping some free space also makes routine updates easier.</p></>}{kind === 'battery' && <><p>Battery capacity is measured in watt-hours. Total system draw includes more than the processor power target: display, memory, storage, fans, radios, and conversion losses all matter. Measured system draw is better than using TDP alone.</p><p>Use a safety buffer because battery health, brightness, background downloads, Bluetooth accessories, and demanding game areas can shorten runtime.</p></>}{kind === 'budget' && <><p>Start with accessories that solve immediate constraints. Storage expands the library; a proper USB-C PD charger keeps the device usable; a case protects it during travel. Docks, controllers, monitors, headsets, and desktop gear should follow actual use.</p><p>Do not budget from sale prices alone. Compatibility, seller quality, warranty, cable rating, device fit, and return terms matter more than saving a few dollars on the wrong accessory.</p></>}
<h2>Useful next step</h2><p>{kind === 'storage' ? <><a href="/gear/microsd-cards/">Compare microSD product families</a> or <a href="/gear/nvme-ssds/">research NVMe SSD upgrades</a>.</> : kind === 'battery' ? <><a href="/gear/power-banks/">Compare USB-C power banks</a>, <a href="/gear/chargers/">chargers</a>, and <a href="/gear/usb-c-cables-adapters/">rated cables</a>.</> : <><a href="/gear/">Browse the full handheld gear library</a> with spec-based product shortlists.</>}</p>
<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>{faq.map(([q,a]) => <><h3>{q}</h3><p>{a}</p></>)}
</div></section>
<script is:inline define:vars={{kind}}>(()=>{const $=id=>document.getElementById(id);function calc(){const a=+$('a').value||0,b=+$('b').value||0,c=+$('c').value||0;let out='',hint='';if(kind==='storage'){const fit=Math.max(0,Math.floor((a-c)/Math.max(1,b)));out=`About ${fit} games fit`;hint=`Assumes ${c}GB reserved for shader cache, saves, OS overhead, and updates.`}else if(kind==='battery'){const hrs=(a*(1-c/100))/Math.max(1,b);out=`About ${hrs.toFixed(1)} hours`;hint='Lower refresh rate, brightness, and total system draw can move this estimate substantially.'}else{out=`Estimated kit total: $${(a+b+c).toFixed(0)}`;hint='Start with storage and a reliable charger before buying cosmetic accessories.'}$('out').textContent=out;$('hint').textContent=hint}['a','b','c'].forEach(id=>$(id).addEventListener('input',calc));calc()})();</script>
</Base>
